{"title": "Characters and Events of Roman History", "description": "Guglielmo Ferrero was an Italian historian and journalist, and this book contains his Lowell Lectures, presented in 1908 at the Lowell Institute in Boston. In his first lecture, Ferrero discusses the \"corruption\" of customs and morals in Rome and compares this to America and Europe of his day; he then discusses key figures and events from Caesar to Nero, and finally considers the role Rome can play in education. Ferrero uses psychological, sociological, and economic lenses in evaluating the world of Rome. (Summary by Mark Harrington)", "duration": 22995, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "18927", "name": "Guglielmo Ferrero"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/characters_2502_librivox/charactereventsromanhistory_2502.jpg", "copyright_year": "1909", "genres": ["Antiquity"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Mark Harrington"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Mark Harrington"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "MaryAnn"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Gretta7"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "\"Corruption\" in Ancient Rome, and Its Counterpart in Modern History", "readers": [4100], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/characters_2502_librivox/characters_01_ferrero_64kb.mp3", "duration": 3173}, {"section": 2, "title": "The History and Legend of Antony and Cleopatra", "readers": [4100], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/characters_2502_librivox/characters_02_ferrero_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2769}, {"section": 3, "title": "The Development of Gaul", "readers": [4100], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/characters_2502_librivox/characters_03_ferrero_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2790}, {"section": 4, "title": "Nero", "readers": [4100], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/characters_2502_librivox/characters_04_ferrero_64kb.mp3", "duration": 3558}, {"section": 5, "title": "Julia and Tiberius", "readers": [4100], "path": "https://www.archive.